
[1]shortness

   SHORT'NESS, n.

   1. The quality of being short in space or time; little length or little
   duration; as the shortness of a journey or of distance; the shortness
   of the days in winter; the shortness of life.

   2. Fewness of words; brevity; conciseness; as th eshortness of an
   essay. The prayers of the church, by reason of their shortness, are
   easy for the memory.

   3. Want of reach or the power of retention; as the shortness of the
   memory.

   4. Deficiency; imperfection; limited extent; as the shortness of our
   reason.
